        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1.get_at((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit_big_rects(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;SDL2 can have more than 16 bits for x, y, width, height.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">big_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">68000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">big_surf_color = (</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">big_surf.fill(big_surf_color)</span>

        <span class="s1">background = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">500</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">500</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">background_color = (</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">background.fill(background_color)</span>

        <span class="s5"># copy parts of the big_surf using more than 16bit parts.</span>
        <span class="s1">background.blit(big_surf</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">area=(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">background.blit(big_surf</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">200</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">200</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">area=(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">background.blit(big_surf</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">300</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">300</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">area=(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">66000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s5"># check that all three areas are drawn.</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">101</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">101</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">big_surf_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">201</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">201</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">big_surf_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">301</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">301</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">big_surf_color)</span>

        <span class="s5"># areas outside the 3 blitted areas not covered by those blits.</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">400</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">301</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">background_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">400</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">201</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">background_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">201</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">background_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">99</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">99</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">background_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(background.get_at((</span><span class="s4">450</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">450</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">background_color)</span>


<span class="s0">class </span><span class="s1">TestSurfaceBlit(unittest.TestCase):</span>
    <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Tests basic blitting functionality and options.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

    <span class="s5"># __doc__ (as of 2008-08-02) for pygame.surface.Surface.blit:</span>

    <span class="s5"># Surface.blit(source, dest, area=None, special_flags = 0): return Rect</span>
    <span class="s5"># draw one image onto another</span>
    <span class="s5">#</span>
    <span class="s5"># Draws a source Surface onto this Surface. The draw can be positioned</span>
    <span class="s5"># with the dest argument. Dest can either be pair of coordinates</span>
    <span class="s5"># representing the upper left corner of the source. A Rect can also be</span>
    <span class="s5"># passed as the destination and the topleft corner of the rectangle</span>
    <span class="s5"># will be used as the position for the blit. The size of the</span>
    <span class="s5"># destination rectangle does not effect the blit.</span>
    <span class="s5">#</span>
    <span class="s5"># An optional area rectangle can be passed as well. This represents a</span>
    <span class="s5"># smaller portion of the source Surface to draw.</span>
    <span class="s5">#</span>
    <span class="s5"># An optional special flags is for passing in new in 1.8.0: BLEND_ADD,</span>
    <span class="s5"># BLEND_SUB, BLEND_MULT, BLEND_MIN, BLEND_MAX new in 1.8.1:</span>
    <span class="s5"># BLEND_RGBA_ADD, BLEND_RGBA_SUB, BLEND_RGBA_MULT, BLEND_RGBA_MIN,</span>
    <span class="s5"># BLEND_RGBA_MAX BLEND_RGB_ADD, BLEND_RGB_SUB, BLEND_RGB_MULT,</span>
    <span class="s5"># BLEND_RGB_MIN, BLEND_RGB_MAX With other special blitting flags</span>
    <span class="s5"># perhaps added in the future.</span>
    <span class="s5">#</span>
    <span class="s5"># The return rectangle is the area of the affected pixels, excluding</span>
    <span class="s5"># any pixels outside the destination Surface, or outside the clipping</span>
    <span class="s5"># area.</span>
    <span class="s5">#</span>
    <span class="s5"># Pixel alphas will be ignored when blitting to an 8 bit Surface.</span>
    <span class="s5"># special_flags new in pygame 1.8.</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">setUp(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Resets starting surfaces.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">self.src_surface = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.src_surface.fill(pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.dst_surface = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.dst_surface.fill(pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit_overflow_coord(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Full coverage w/ overflow, specified with Coordinate&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">result = self.dst_surface.blit(self.src_surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(result</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Rect)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(result.size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">k </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">[(x</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">x) </span><span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">x </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">)]:</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(self.dst_surface.get_at(k)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit_overflow_rect(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Full coverage w/ overflow, specified with a Rect&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">result = self.dst_surface.blit(self.src_surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Rect(-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">300</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">300</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(result</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Rect)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(result.size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">k </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">[(x</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">x) </span><span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">x </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">)]:</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit__SRCALPHA_opaque_source(self):</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit__blit_to_self(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Test that blit operation works on self, alpha value is 
        correct, and that no RGB distortion occurs.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">test_surface = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">area = test_surface.get_rect()</span>

        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">pt</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_color </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">test_utils.gradient(area.width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">area.height):</span>
            <span class="s1">test_surface.set_at(pt</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_color)</span>

        <span class="s1">reference_surface = test_surface.copy()</span>

        <span class="s1">test_surface.blit(test_surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">x </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(area.width):</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">y </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(area.height):</span>
                <span class="s1">(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a) = reference_color = reference_surface.get_at((x</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">y))</span>
                <span class="s1">expected_color = (r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(a + (a * ((</span><span class="s4">256 </span><span class="s1">- a) // </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">))))</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(reference_color</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_color)</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(reference_surface.get_rect()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_surface.get_rect())</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit__SRCALPHA_to_SRCALPHA_non_zero(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Tests blitting a nonzero alpha surface to another nonzero alpha surface 
        both straight alpha compositing method. Test is fuzzy (+/- 1/256) to account for 
        different implementations in SDL1 and SDL2. 
        &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

        <span class="s1">size = (</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">check_color_diff(color1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color2):</span>
            <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Returns True if two colors are within (1, 1, 1, 1) of each other.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">val </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">color1 - color2:</span>
                <span class="s0">if </span><span class="s1">abs(val) &gt; </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                    <span class="s0">return False</span>
            <span class="s0">return True</span>

        <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">high_a_onto_low(high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low):</span>
            <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Tests straight alpha case. Source is low alpha, destination is high alpha&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_surface = pygame.Surface(size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_surface = high_alpha_surface.copy()</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_color = Color(</span>
                <span class="s1">(high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">high)</span>
            <span class="s1">)  </span><span class="s5"># Injecting some RGB variance.</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_color = Color((high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low))</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_surface.fill(high_alpha_color)</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_surface.fill(low_alpha_color)</span>

            <span class="s1">high_alpha_surface.blit(low_alpha_surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">expected_color = low_alpha_color + Color(</span>
                <span class="s1">tuple(</span>
                    <span class="s1">((x * (</span><span class="s4">255 </span><span class="s1">- low_alpha_color.a)) // </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">x </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">high_alpha_color</span>
                <span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(</span>
                <span class="s1">check_color_diff(high_alpha_surface.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_color)</span>
            <span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">low_a_onto_high(high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low):</span>
            <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Tests straight alpha case. Source is high alpha, destination is low alpha&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_surface = pygame.Surface(size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_surface = high_alpha_surface.copy()</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_color = Color(</span>
                <span class="s1">(high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">high)</span>
            <span class="s1">)  </span><span class="s5"># Injecting some RGB variance.</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_color = Color((high</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low))</span>
            <span class="s1">high_alpha_surface.fill(high_alpha_color)</span>
            <span class="s1">low_alpha_surface.fill(low_alpha_color)</span>

            <span class="s1">low_alpha_surface.blit(high_alpha_surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">expected_color = high_alpha_color + Color(</span>
                <span class="s1">tuple(</span>
                    <span class="s1">((x * (</span><span class="s4">255 </span><span class="s1">- high_alpha_color.a)) // </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">) </span><span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">x </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">low_alpha_color</span>
                <span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(</span>
                <span class="s1">check_color_diff(low_alpha_surface.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_color)</span>
            <span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">low_a </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s1">):</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">high_a </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                <span class="s1">high_a_onto_low(high_a</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low_a)</span>
                <span class="s1">low_a_onto_high(high_a</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">low_a)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_blit__SRCALPHA32_to_8(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># Bug: fatal</span>
        <span class="s5"># SDL_DisplayConvert segfaults when video is uninitialized.</span>
        <span class="s1">target = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">11</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">test_color = target.get_palette_at(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">source = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">source.set_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_color)</span>
        <span class="s1">target.blit(source</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>


<span class="s0">class </span><span class="s1">GeneralSurfaceTests(AssertRaisesRegexMixin</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">unittest.TestCase):</span>
    <span class="s1">@unittest.skipIf(</span>
        <span class="s1">os.environ.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;SDL_VIDEODRIVER&quot;</span><span class="s1">) == </span><span class="s2">&quot;dummy&quot;</span><span class="s0">,</span>
        <span class="s2">'requires a non-&quot;dummy&quot; SDL_VIDEODRIVER'</span><span class="s0">,</span>
    <span class="s1">)</span>
    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_image_convert_bug_131(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># bug #131: Unable to Surface.convert(32) some 1-bit images.</span>
        <span class="s5"># https://github.com/pygame/pygame/issues/131</span>

        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">640</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">480</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">im = pygame.image.load(example_path(os.path.join(</span><span class="s2">&quot;data&quot;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;city.png&quot;</span><span class="s1">)))</span>
            <span class="s1">im2 = pygame.image.load(example_path(os.path.join(</span><span class="s2">&quot;data&quot;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;brick.png&quot;</span><span class="s1">)))</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(im.get_palette()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(im2.get_palette()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)))</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(repr(im.convert(</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;Surface(24x24x32 SW)&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(repr(im2.convert(</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;Surface(469x137x32 SW)&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Ensure a palette format to palette format works.</span>
            <span class="s1">im3 = im.convert(</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(repr(im3)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;&lt;Surface(24x24x8 SW)&gt;&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(im3.get_palette()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">im.get_palette())</span>

        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_convert_init(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure initialization exceptions are raised 
        for surf.convert().&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertRaisesRegex(pygame.error</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;display initialized&quot;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf.convert)</span>

        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s0">if </span><span class="s1">os.environ.get(</span><span class="s2">&quot;SDL_VIDEODRIVER&quot;</span><span class="s1">) != </span><span class="s2">&quot;dummy&quot;</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                    <span class="s1">surf.convert(</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
                    <span class="s1">surf.convert(pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)))</span>
                <span class="s0">except </span><span class="s1">pygame.error:</span>
                    <span class="s1">self.fail(</span><span class="s2">&quot;convert() should not raise an exception here.&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertRaisesRegex(pygame.error</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;No video mode&quot;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf.convert)</span>

            <span class="s1">pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">640</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">480</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s1">surf.convert()</span>
            <span class="s0">except </span><span class="s1">pygame.error:</span>
                <span class="s1">self.fail(</span><span class="s2">&quot;convert() should not raise an exception here.&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_convert_alpha_SRCALPHA(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure that the surface returned by surf.convert_alpha() 
        has alpha blending enabled&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">640</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">480</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">s1 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s5"># s2=pygame.Surface((100,100), pygame.SRCALPHA, 32)</span>
            <span class="s1">s1_alpha = s1.convert_alpha()</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1_alpha.get_flags() &amp; SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_src_alpha_issue_1289(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;blit should be white.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">surf1 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf1.fill((</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">surf2 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf2.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf2.blit(surf1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf1.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf2.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_src_alpha_compatible_16bit(self):</span>

        <span class="s5">#     pprint(results)</span>

        <span class="s1">nums = [</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">65</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">126</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">127</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">199</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">254</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">]</span>
        <span class="s1">results = {}</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">dst_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_a </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">zip(nums</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">reversed(nums)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">reversed(nums)):</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">src_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_a </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">zip(nums</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">reversed(nums)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">nums):</span>
                <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.subTest(</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_r=src_r</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_b=src_b</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_a=src_a</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_r=dst_r</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_b=dst_b</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_a=dst_a</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                <span class="s1">):</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s1">)</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_surf.fill((src_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_a))</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s1">)</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_surf.fill((dst_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_a))</span>

                    <span class="s1">dest_surf.blit(src_surf</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
                    <span class="s1">key = ((dst_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_a)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(src_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_a))</span>
                    <span class="s1">results[key] = dest_surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">65</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">33</span><span class="s1">))</span>
                    <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(results[key]</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">results_expected[key])</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(results</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">results_expected)</span>

        <span class="s5"># chosen because they contain edge cases.</span>
        <span class="s1">nums = [</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">65</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">126</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">127</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">199</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">254</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">]</span>

                <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.subTest(</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_r=src_r</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_b=src_b</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_a=src_a</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_r=dst_r</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_b=dst_b</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                    <span class="s1">dest_a=dst_a</span><span class="s0">,</span>
                <span class="s1">):</span>
                    <span class="s1">src_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">66</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

                    <span class="s1">key = ((dst_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">dst_a)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(src_r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">src_a))</span>

                    <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(results[key]</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">results_expected[key])</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_opaque_destination_blit_with_set_alpha(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># no set_alpha()</span>
        <span class="s1">src_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s1">dest_surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">dest_surf.fill((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">no_surf_alpha_col = dest_surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">dest_surf.fill((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">surf_alpha_col = dest_surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(no_surf_alpha_col</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf_alpha_col)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">todo_test_convert(self):</span>

        <span class="s5"># __doc__ (as of 2008-08-02) for pygame.surface.Surface.convert:</span>

        <span class="s5"># Surface.convert(Surface): return Surface</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface.convert(depth, flags=0): return Surface</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface.convert(masks, flags=0): return Surface</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface.convert(): return Surface</span>
        <span class="s5"># change the pixel format of an image</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># Creates a new copy of the Surface with the pixel format changed. The</span>
        <span class="s5"># new pixel format can be determined from another existing Surface.</span>
        <span class="s5"># Otherwise depth, flags, and masks arguments can be used, similar to</span>
        <span class="s5"># the pygame.Surface() call.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># If no arguments are passed the new Surface will have the same pixel</span>
        <span class="s5"># format as the display Surface. This is always the fastest format for</span>
        <span class="s5"># blitting. It is a good idea to convert all Surfaces before they are</span>
        <span class="s5"># blitted many times.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># The converted Surface will have no pixel alphas. They will be</span>
        <span class="s5"># stripped if the original had them. See Surface.convert_alpha() for</span>
        <span class="s5"># preserving or creating per-pixel alphas.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>

        <span class="s1">self.fail()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_convert__pixel_format_as_surface_subclass(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure convert accepts a Surface subclass argument.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">expected_size = (</span><span class="s4">23</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">17</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">convert_surface = SurfaceSubclass(expected_size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">depth_surface = SurfaceSubclass((</span><span class="s4">31</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">61</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">surface = convert_surface.convert(depth_surface)</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNot(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth_surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNot(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">convert_surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SurfaceSubclass)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_size()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_size)</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_convert_alpha(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure the surface returned by surf.convert_alpha 
        has alpha values added&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">640</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">480</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">s1 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s1_alpha = pygame.Surface.convert_alpha(s1)</span>

            <span class="s1">s2 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s2_alpha = s2.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">s3 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s3_alpha = s3.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">s4 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">12</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s4_alpha = s4.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">s5 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s5_alpha = s5.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">s6 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s6_alpha = s6.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">s7 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">s7_alpha = s7.convert_alpha()</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s2_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s3_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s4_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s5_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s6_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s7_alpha.get_alpha()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s1_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s2_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s3_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s4_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s5_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s6_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s6_alpha.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">surface = pygame.display.set_mode()</span>
                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
                <span class="s1">surface.convert_alpha()</span>

        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_convert_alpha__pixel_format_as_surface_subclass(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure convert_alpha accepts a Surface subclass argument.&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">expected_size = (</span><span class="s4">23</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">17</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">convert_surface = SurfaceSubclass(expected_size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">depth_surface = SurfaceSubclass((</span><span class="s4">31</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">57</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">60</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">60</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># This is accepted as an argument, but its values are ignored.</span>
            <span class="s5"># See issue #599.</span>
            <span class="s1">surface = convert_surface.convert_alpha(depth_surface)</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNot(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth_surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNot(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">convert_surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Surface)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SurfaceSubclass)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_size()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_size)</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_abs_offset(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">parent = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Stack bunch of subsurfaces</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_1 = parent.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">34</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">37</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_2 = sub_level_1.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">30</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">29</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_3 = sub_level_2.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">7</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">20</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">21</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_4 = sub_level_3.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">6</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">14</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">14</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_5 = sub_level_4.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">6</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">4</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># Parent is always (0, 0)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(parent.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s5"># Total offset: (0+2, 0+2) = (2, 2)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_1.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s5"># Total offset: (0+2+0, 0+2+0) = (2, 2)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_2.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s5"># Total offset: (0+2+0+3, 0+2+0+7) = (5, 9)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_3.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">9</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s5"># Total offset: (0+2+0+3+6, 0+2+0+7+1) = (11, 10)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_4.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">11</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s5"># Total offset: (0+2+0+3+6+5, 0+2+0+7+1+6) = (16, 16)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_5.get_abs_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">surface = pygame.display.set_mode()</span>
                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
                <span class="s1">surface.get_abs_offset()</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_abs_parent(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">parent = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Stack bunch of subsurfaces</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_1 = parent.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_2 = sub_level_1.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">12</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">12</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_3 = sub_level_2.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">9</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">9</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_4 = sub_level_3.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_5 = sub_level_4.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">4</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">sub_level_6 = sub_level_5.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># Can't have subsurfaces bigger than parents</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(ValueError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent.subsurface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(ValueError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">sub_level_3.subsurface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">11</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(ValueError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">sub_level_6.subsurface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># Calling get_abs_parent on parent should return itself</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(parent.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent)</span>

            <span class="s5"># On subclass &quot;depth&quot; of 1, get_abs_parent and get_parent should return the same</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_1.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">sub_level_1.get_parent())</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_2.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_3.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_4.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_level_5.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">parent)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(</span>
                <span class="s1">sub_level_6.get_abs_parent()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">sub_level_6.get_parent().get_abs_parent()</span>
            <span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">surface = pygame.display.set_mode()</span>
                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
                <span class="s1">surface.get_abs_parent()</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_at(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">c00 = pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">c01 = pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">c10 = pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">50</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">c11 = pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">4</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">6</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c00)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c01)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_at((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c10)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_at((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c11)</span>
        <span class="s1">c = surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(c</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(c</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c00)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c01)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c10)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c11)</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">p </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">[(-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)]:</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(IndexError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf.get_at</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">p)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_at_mapped(self):</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_bitsize(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>

            <span class="s1">expected_depth = </span><span class="s4">16</span>
            <span class="s1">surface = pygame.Surface(expected_size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_depth)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_size()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_size)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_depth)</span>

            <span class="s1">expected_depth = </span><span class="s4">15</span>
            <span class="s1">surface = pygame.Surface(expected_size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_depth)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_size()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_size)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_bitsize()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_depth)</span>
            <span class="s5"># Check for invalid depths</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(</span>
                <span class="s1">ValueError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_size</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">expected_depth</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(</span>

            <span class="s1">)</span>

                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_colorkey(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s5"># if set_colorkey is not used</span>
            <span class="s1">s = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">800</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">600</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNone(s.get_colorkey())</span>

            <span class="s5"># if set_colorkey is used</span>
            <span class="s1">s.set_colorkey(</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsNone(s.get_colorkey())</span>

            <span class="s5"># setting up remainder of tests...</span>
            <span class="s1">r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a = </span><span class="s4">20</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">40</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">60</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">12</span>
            <span class="s1">colorkey = pygame.Color(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b)</span>
            <span class="s1">s.set_colorkey(colorkey)</span>

            <span class="s5"># test for ideal case</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s.get_colorkey()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># test for if the color_key is set using pygame.RLEACCEL</span>
            <span class="s1">s.set_colorkey(colorkey</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.RLEACCEL)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s.get_colorkey()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># test for if the color key is not what's expected</span>
            <span class="s1">s.set_colorkey(pygame.Color(r + </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g + </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b + </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertNotEqual(s.get_colorkey()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">s.set_colorkey(pygame.Color(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a))</span>
            <span class="s5"># regardless of whether alpha is not 255</span>
            <span class="s5"># colorkey returned from surface is always 255</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s.get_colorkey()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(r</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s5"># test for using method after display.quit() is called...</span>
            <span class="s1">s = pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">200</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">200</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">s.get_colorkey()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_height(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">sizes = ((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">119</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">119</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">height </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">sizes:</span>
