            <span class="s1">found_height = surf.get_height()</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(height</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">found_height)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_locked(self):</span>
        <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surface):</span>
            <span class="s1">newSurf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s1">newSurf.blit(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s0">except </span><span class="s1">pygame.error:</span>
                <span class="s0">return True</span>
            <span class="s0">else</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s0">return False</span>

        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface should lock</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Locked</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface should unlock</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>

        <span class="s5"># Check multiple locks</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Locked</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Locked</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>

        <span class="s5"># Check many locks</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s1">):</span>
            <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Locked</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s1">):</span>
            <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertFalse(surf.get_locked())  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>

        <span class="s5"># Unlocking an unlocked surface</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIs(surf.get_locked()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">blit_locked_test(surf))  </span><span class="s5"># Unlocked</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_locks(self):</span>

        <span class="s5"># __doc__ (as of 2008-08-02) for pygame.surface.Surface.get_locks:</span>

        <span class="s5"># Surface.get_locks(): return tuple</span>
        <span class="s5"># Gets the locks for the Surface</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># Returns the currently existing locks for the Surface.</span>

        <span class="s5"># test on a surface that is not initially locked</span>
        <span class="s1">surface = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">())</span>

        <span class="s5"># test on the same surface after it has been locked</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(surface</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">))</span>

        <span class="s5"># test on the same surface after it has been unlocked</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">())</span>

        <span class="s5"># test with PixelArray initialization: locks surface</span>
        <span class="s1">pxarray = pygame.PixelArray(surface)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertNotEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">())</span>

        <span class="s5"># closing the PixelArray releases the surface lock</span>
        <span class="s1">pxarray.close()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">())</span>

        <span class="s5"># AttributeError raised when called on invalid object type (i.e. not a pygame.Surface object)</span>
        <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(AttributeError):</span>
            <span class="s2">&quot;DUMMY&quot;</span><span class="s1">.get_locks()</span>

        <span class="s5"># test multiple locks and unlocks on the same surface</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surface</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surface))</span>

        <span class="s1">surface.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(surface</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surface.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surface.get_locks()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">())</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_losses(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;Ensure a surface's losses can be retrieved&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s5"># Masks for different color component configurations</span>
            <span class="s1">mask8 = (</span><span class="s4">224</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">28</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">mask15 = (</span><span class="s4">31744</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">992</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">31</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">mask16 = (</span><span class="s4">63488</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2016</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">31</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">mask24 = (</span><span class="s4">4278190080</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16711680</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">65280</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">mask32 = (</span><span class="s4">4278190080</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16711680</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">65280</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Surfaces with standard depths and masks</span>
            <span class="s1">display_surf = pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_8bit = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">masks=mask8)</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_15bit = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">masks=mask15)</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_16bit = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">masks=mask16)</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_24bit = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">masks=mask24)</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_32bit = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">masks=mask32)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Test output is correct type, length, and value range</span>
            <span class="s1">losses = surf.get_losses()</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(losses</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">tuple)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(len(losses)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">4</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">loss </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">losses:</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(loss</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">int)</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertGreaterEqual(loss</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertLessEqual(loss</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>

            <span class="s5"># Test each surface for correct losses</span>
            <span class="s5"># Display surface losses gives idea of default surface losses</span>
            <span class="s0">if </span><span class="s1">display_surf.get_losses() == (</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(losses</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s0">elif </span><span class="s1">display_surf.get_losses() == (</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">):</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(losses</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf_8bit.get_losses()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">6</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf_15bit.get_losses()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf_16bit.get_losses()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf_24bit.get_losses()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf_32bit.get_losses()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># Method should fail when display is not initialized</span>
            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">surface = pygame.display.set_mode((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
                <span class="s1">surface.get_losses()</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

            <span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0xF800</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x07E0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x001F</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x0000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">,</span>
            <span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0xFF0000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x00FF00</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x0000FF</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x000000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">,</span>

        <span class="s1">]</span>
        <span class="s1">depths = [</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">12</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">15</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">16</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">]</span>

            <span class="s0">if </span><span class="s1">depth == </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">:</span>
                <span class="s1">expected = (</span><span class="s4">0x00</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x00</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x00</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0x00</span><span class="s1">)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_offset(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;get_offset returns the (0,0) if surface is not a child 
        returns the position of child subsurface inside of parent 
        &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">pygame.display.init()</span>
        <span class="s0">try</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s5"># subsurface offset test</span>
            <span class="s1">subsurf = surf.subsurface(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s1">)</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(subsurf.get_offset()</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">))</span>

            <span class="s0">with </span><span class="s1">self.assertRaises(pygame.error):</span>
                <span class="s1">surface = pygame.display.set_mode()</span>
                <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>
                <span class="s1">surface.get_offset()</span>
        <span class="s0">finally</span><span class="s1">:</span>
            <span class="s1">pygame.display.quit()</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_palette(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">palette = [Color(i</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">i</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">i) </span><span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">i </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">range(</span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">)]</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_palette(palette)</span>
        <span class="s1">palette2 = surf.get_palette()</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(len(palette2)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">len(palette))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">c2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">zip(palette2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">palette):</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(c2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c)</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">c </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">palette2:</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(c</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Color)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_palette_at(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># See also test_get_palette</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">color = pygame.Color(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">3</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_palette_at(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>
        <span class="s1">color2 = surf.get_palette_at(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertIsInstance(color2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">pygame.Color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(color2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(IndexError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf.get_palette_at</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertRaises(IndexError</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">surf.get_palette_at</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_pitch(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># Test get_pitch() on several surfaces of varying size/depth</span>
        <span class="s1">sizes = ((</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">7</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">33</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">33</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">7</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">734</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">734</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">734</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">734</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">depths = [</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">]</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">height </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">sizes:</span>
            <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">depth </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">depths:</span>
                <span class="s5"># Test get_pitch() on parent surface</span>
                <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">height)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=depth)</span>
                <span class="s1">buff = surf.get_buffer()</span>
                <span class="s1">pitch = buff.length / surf.get_height()</span>
                <span class="s1">test_pitch = surf.get_pitch()</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(pitch</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_pitch)</span>
                <span class="s5"># Test get_pitch() on subsurface with same rect as parent</span>
                <span class="s1">rect1 = surf.get_rect()</span>
                <span class="s1">subsurf1 = surf.subsurface(rect1)</span>
                <span class="s1">sub_buff1 = subsurf1.get_buffer()</span>
                <span class="s1">sub_pitch1 = sub_buff1.length / subsurf1.get_height()</span>
                <span class="s1">test_sub_pitch1 = subsurf1.get_pitch()</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_pitch1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_sub_pitch1)</span>
                <span class="s5"># Test get_pitch on subsurface with modified rect</span>
                <span class="s1">rect2 = rect1.inflate(-width / </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">-height / </span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">)</span>
                <span class="s1">subsurf2 = surf.subsurface(rect2)</span>
                <span class="s1">sub_buff2 = subsurf2.get_buffer()</span>
                <span class="s1">sub_pitch2 = sub_buff2.length / float(subsurf2.get_height())</span>
                <span class="s1">test_sub_pitch2 = subsurf2.get_pitch()</span>
                <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(sub_pitch2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">test_sub_pitch2)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_shifts(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot; 
        Tests whether Surface.get_shifts returns proper 
        RGBA shifts under various conditions. 
        &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s5"># __doc__ (as of 2008-08-02) for pygame.surface.Surface.get_shifts:</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface.get_shifts(): return (R, G, B, A)</span>
        <span class="s5"># the bit shifts needed to convert between color and mapped integer.</span>
        <span class="s5"># Returns the pixel shifts need to convert between each color and a</span>
        <span class="s5"># mapped integer.</span>
        <span class="s5"># This value is not needed for normal Pygame usage.</span>

        <span class="s5"># Test for SDL2 on surfaces with various depths and alpha on/off</span>
        <span class="s1">depths = [</span><span class="s4">8</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">24</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">]</span>
        <span class="s1">alpha = </span><span class="s4">128</span>
        <span class="s1">off = </span><span class="s0">None</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">bit_depth </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">depths:</span>
            <span class="s1">surface = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">depth=bit_depth)</span>
            <span class="s1">surface.set_alpha(alpha)</span>
            <span class="s1">r1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a1 = surface.get_shifts()</span>
            <span class="s1">surface.set_alpha(off)</span>
            <span class="s1">r2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a2 = surface.get_shifts()</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual((r1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a1)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(r2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">g2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">b2</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">a2))</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_get_size(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">sizes = ((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">119</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">10</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5000</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">1221</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">99</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">999</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">height </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">sizes:</span>

            <span class="s1">found_size = surf.get_size()</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertEqual((width</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">height)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">found_size)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_lock(self):</span>

        <span class="s5"># __doc__ (as of 2008-08-02) for pygame.surface.Surface.lock:</span>

        <span class="s5"># Surface.lock(): return None</span>
        <span class="s5"># lock the Surface memory for pixel access</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># Lock the pixel data of a Surface for access. On accelerated</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surfaces, the pixel data may be stored in volatile video memory or</span>
        <span class="s5"># nonlinear compressed forms. When a Surface is locked the pixel</span>
        <span class="s5"># memory becomes available to access by regular software. Code that</span>
        <span class="s5"># reads or writes pixel values will need the Surface to be locked.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surfaces should not remain locked for more than necessary. A locked</span>
        <span class="s5"># Surface can often not be displayed or managed by Pygame.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># Not all Surfaces require locking. The Surface.mustlock() method can</span>
        <span class="s5"># determine if it is actually required. There is no performance</span>
        <span class="s5"># penalty for locking and unlocking a Surface that does not need it.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># All pygame functions will automatically lock and unlock the Surface</span>
        <span class="s5"># data as needed. If a section of code is going to make calls that</span>
        <span class="s5"># will repeatedly lock and unlock the Surface many times, it can be</span>
        <span class="s5"># helpful to wrap the block inside a lock and unlock pair.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>
        <span class="s5"># It is safe to nest locking and unlocking calls. The surface will</span>
        <span class="s5"># only be unlocked after the final lock is released.</span>
        <span class="s5">#</span>

        <span class="s5"># Basic</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>

        <span class="s5"># Nested</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertFalse(surf.get_locked())</span>

        <span class="s5"># Already Locked</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">100</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.lock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf.get_locked())</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.unlock()</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertFalse(surf.get_locked())</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_map_rgb(self):</span>
        <span class="s1">color = Color(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">64</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">5</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">c = surf.map_rgb(color)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.unmap_rgb(c)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>

        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.fill(c)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>

        <span class="s1">surf.fill((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf.set_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">c)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(surf.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">color)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_mustlock(self):</span>
        <span class="s5"># Test that subsurfaces mustlock</span>
        <span class="s1">surf = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1024</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1024</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">subsurf = surf.subsurface((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1024</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1024</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(subsurf.mustlock())</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertFalse(surf.mustlock())</span>
        <span class="s5"># Tests nested subsurfaces</span>
        <span class="s1">rects = ((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">512</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">512</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">256</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">surf_stack = []</span>
        <span class="s1">surf_stack.append(surf)</span>
        <span class="s1">surf_stack.append(subsurf)</span>
        <span class="s0">for </span><span class="s1">rect </span><span class="s0">in </span><span class="s1">rects:</span>
            <span class="s1">surf_stack.append(surf_stack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">].subsurface(rect))</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf_stack[-</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">].mustlock())</span>
            <span class="s1">self.assertTrue(surf_stack[-</span><span class="s4">2</span><span class="s1">].mustlock())</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_set_alpha_none(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;surf.set_alpha(None) disables blending&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">s = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">s.fill((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">128</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">s.set_alpha(</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(</span><span class="s0">None, </span><span class="s1">s.get_alpha())</span>

        <span class="s1">s2 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">s2.fill((</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">s2.blit(s</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertEqual(s2.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;the red component should be 0&quot;</span><span class="s1">)</span>

    <span class="s0">def </span><span class="s1">test_set_alpha_value(self):</span>
        <span class="s3">&quot;&quot;&quot;surf.set_alpha(x), where x != None, enables blending&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">s = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s1">s.set_alpha(</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">)</span>

        <span class="s1">s2 = pygame.Surface((</span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">1</span><span class="s1">)</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">SRCALPHA</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">32</span><span class="s1">)</span>
        <span class="s1">s2.fill((</span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">255</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">s2.blit(s</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">(</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))</span>
        <span class="s1">self.assertGreater(</span>
            <span class="s1">s2.get_at((</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">))[</span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s1">]</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s4">0</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s2">&quot;the red component should be above 0&quot;</span>
        <span class="s1">)</span>
